The goal of triangulation is to use two cameras in known offset positions to find the location of an object. The above figures are valid for both the top view (x-z displacement) and side view (y-z displacement) of the vision fields of two offset cameras. Each set of these figures can solve for the object\u8217\'92s displacement in the given dimensions. If the cameras only have a horizontal offset, the calculations only need to be preformed in the x/z axis, but if any y offset is introduced, calculations must be preformed in both dimensions to obtain a 3-dimensional knowledge of the object\u8217\'92s location. A slightly different process, not defined in this document, must take place if any z displacement is introduced.}
